# Domain advisor — Application Security (APP)

**Spec:** `docs/project_spec.md` **§9 TASK-016** (APP). **Input contract:** `docs/ai/references/customer-state-update-delta.md`.

## When this rule applies

Use when the **orchestrator** (or user) assigns the **APP** pass after SOC: analyze **`CustomerStateUpdate.json`** (extractor delta).

## Wiz product documentation

- Use a **separate** MCP server for Wiz docs (**`wiz-local`** or user-configured name).
- Invoke its document search tool (**name varies by server** — e.g. **`wiz_search_wiz_docs`**). No secrets in prompts or rules.

### Retrieval hybrid (prestonotes vs wiz-local)

- **`wiz_knowledge_search`**: local Chroma over cached markdown; **`include_staleness=true`** when freshness matters.
- **wiz-local**: live **`wiz_search_wiz_docs`** / WIN APIs for authoritative docs.
- Prefer **vector first**; if weak or **stale**, targeted **wiz-local**, update cache (**`docs/ai/playbooks/refresh-wiz-doc-cache.md`**), then **`refresh_wiz_vector_index`** after approval.

## Domain scope (APP only)

Own **secure SDLC**, **code security**, **secrets in code**, **dependency / supply-chain risk**, **container/K8s application images**, **IaC misconfigurations from a developer workflow lens**, and **developer-centric remediation** — not SOC detection operations, classic enterprise VM program management, pure attack-surface **external** exposure mapping (ASM), or ML model governance (AI advisor).

## Analysis steps

1. Parse **`CustomerStateUpdate.json`**; select APP-scoped gaps/challenges.
2. Query **wiz-local** (or equivalent) for Wiz capabilities tied to those gaps (Code, CI/CD integration, developer workflows, etc.).
3. Map credible doc-backed capabilities to gaps; push unmapped items to **`no_match_gaps`**.

## Output JSON (single object)

| Key | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `domain` | string | Always **`"app"`** |
| `gaps_analyzed` | string[] | APP-scoped gap/challenge ids or labels evaluated |
| `recommendations` | array | See below |
| `no_match_gaps` | string[] | In-scope items with **no** credible Wiz mapping |

**Each `recommendations[]` element:**

| Key | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `capability` | string | Specific Wiz capability (from retrieved docs) |
| `rationale` | string | **2–3 sentences** linking customer gap → capability |
| `doc_link` | string | URL from search, or placeholder if missing |
| `confidence` | number | **0–1** |

## Discipline

- Avoid overlapping **SOC** (runtime SOC operations) or **VULN** (enterprise vuln program / SLAs) framing unless the gap is clearly developer-pipeline-centric.
- Read-only pass; writes only after user approval in orchestrator steps.
